      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Since the resources look healthy, your hunch about the networking layer, perhaps driven by a load balancer timeout, is very smart. Check the Connection Idle Timeout settings on your Application Load Balancer across all target groups; a cut-off might prematurely sever connections perceived as inactive by the ALB. To definitively separate this, try running a load test that mimics peak traffic but introduces a *lower* steady application load to see if the resets persist without the high traffic spike. This helps determine if the sheer volume or the *idle* nature of the traffic is triggering the issue.",
      "source": "target",
